14-1-2. Eligible Programs and Projects.
(a)	Individuals and organizations are eligible to apply for grants from the city for programs, projects, and operational support that stimulates or promotes arts, culture, and creativity for the people of the city, including, without limitation:
(1)	Visual arts and crafts;
(2)	Music;
(3)	Theater;
(4)	Literary arts;
(5)	Dance;
(6)	Time-based media, film/video, digital art, and web-based art;
(7)	Educational activities including lectures, classes and field trips;
(8)	Festivals, exhibitions, and art in public places;
(9)	History and heritage;
(10)	Design, architecture, and landscape; and
(11)	The contemplative arts.
(b)	Any performance, production, lecture, class, reading, exhibition, festival, film, organization, or other program funded in whole or in part by a grant under this chapter shall primarily be located, held, or shown within the Boulder Valley as defined by the then current version of the Boulder Valley Comprehensive Plan.
Ordinance No. 8207 (2017)
